Do you know why you won't see any more a-plants, except in centrally managed economies or government utilities?<br>
<br>
Because of reforms, generation systems are now &quot;merchant&quot; plants. They must be built AT SHAREHOLDER RISK, and the power then sold into a competitive market. Never has an atomic plant been built under the requirements of being a merchant plant and having to meet even the most minimum standards of economic tests.<br>
